<subSubSection id="C37E65682B76FFB926F1FC33FBF6872E" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDB36E32B76FFB926F1FC33FBF6872E" blockId="18.[151,1437,970,1463]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B76FFB926F1FC33FE9C81EA" bold="true" box="[151,273,970,995]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body cylindrical of variable size, from relatively medium-sized to large, compared to most syllids. Subpentagonal prostomium, with 1 pair of palps totally free from each other or fused at bases, 3 antennae, 2 pairs of eyes and, sometimes, 1 pair of anterior eyespots. Peristomium usually shorter than segments, with 2 pairs of peristomial cirri; border between prostomium and peristomium usually with conspicuous nuchal organs, as 1 pair of ciliated grooves. Antennae, peristomial cirri, dorsal cirri throughout and anal cirri moniliform; ventral cirri short, digitiform. Parapodia with compound falcigers, some taxa with secondarily simple chaetae, due to fusion between shaft and blade, or loss of blade; spiniger-like chaetae frequently present; dorsal and ventral simple chaetae usually present on posterior chaetigers. Pharynx with large tooth on anterior border or slightly posteriorly to opening, trepan absent (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF54B122B76FFB92727FB13FD11870A" author="Nogueira" box="[321,668,1258,1283]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" refString="Nogueira, J. M. M. &amp; San Martin, G. (2002) Species of Syllis Savigny in Lamarck, 1818 (Polychaeta: Syllidae) living in corals in the state of Sao Paulo, southeastern Brazil. Beaufortia, 52 (7), 57 - 93." type="journal article" year="2002">Nogueira &amp; San Martín 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF54B122B76FFB924CAFB13FBA8870A" author="Nogueira" box="[684,1061,1258,1283]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" refString="Nogueira, J. M. M. &amp; Yunda-Guarin, G. (2008) A new species of Syllis (Polychaeta: Syllidae: Syllinae) from off Fortaleza, north-eastern Brazil. Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom, 88 (7), 1391 - 1399. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0025315408002099" type="journal article" year="2008">Nogueira &amp; Yunda-Guarin 2008</bibRefCitation>
). Reproduction by stolonization, with stolons with different morphologies, according to species. Some species viviparous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37E65682B76FFB926A1FACBFB4687BF" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BDB36E32B76FFB926A1FACBFB4687BF" blockId="18.[151,1437,970,1463]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B76FFB926A1FACBFEB68742" bold="true" box="[199,315,1330,1355]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Remarks.</emphasis>
The largest genus in the family, 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D602B76FFB924C9FACBFD618742" box="[687,748,1330,1355]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B76FFB924C9FACBFD618742" box="[687,748,1330,1355]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Syllis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as currently conceived, seems to be paraphyletic, according to phylogenetic analyses performed on the family (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF54B122B76FFB924A8FAAFFC258766" author="Aguado" box="[718,936,1366,1391]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" refString="Aguado, M. T., Nygren, A &amp; Siddall, M. E. (2007) Phylogeny of Syllidae (Polychaeta) based on combined molecular analysis of nuclear and mitochondrial genes. Cladistics, 23, 552 - 564." type="journal article" year="2007">
Aguado 
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B76FFB92549FAAEFCEA8766" box="[815,871,1366,1391]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF54B122B76FFB925D5FAAEFC7D8766" author="Aguado" box="[947,1008,1367,1391]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" refString="Aguado, M. T., San Martin, G. &amp; Siddall, M. E. (2012) Systematics and evolution of syllids (Annelida, Syllidae). Cladistics, 28, 234 - 250." type="journal article" year="2012">2012</bibRefCitation>
). However, until more detailed studies are made specifically on this genus, we follow herein the opinion of most authors (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF54B122B76FFB92209FA82FAA3879A" author="San" box="[1135,1326,1403,1427]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" refString="San Martin, G. (2003) Annelida Polychaeta II: Syllidae. In: Ramos, M. A. (Ed.), Fauna Iberica. Lol. 21. Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales, CSIC, Madrid, pp. 1 - 544." type="journal article" year="2003">San Martín 2003</bibRefCitation>
; Álvarez- Campos 
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B76FFB9269CFA66FEBF87BE" box="[250,306,1438,1463]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">et al.</emphasis>
2015a, b), considering 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D602B76FFB9245CFA67FCF487BE" authority="Langerhans, 1879" authorityName="Langerhans" authorityYear="1879" box="[570,889,1438,1463]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Typosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B76FFB9245CFA67FD2487BE" box="[570,681,1438,1463]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Typosyllis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF54B122B76FFB924D6FA67FCF487BE" author="Langerhans" box="[688,889,1438,1463]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" refString="Langerhans, P. (1879) Die Wurmfauna von Madeira [part I]. Zeitschrift fur wissenschaftliche Zoologie, 32 (4), 513 - 592." type="journal article" year="1879">Langerhans, 1879</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C644D602B76FFB922EEFA67FB4987BE" box="[1160,1220,1438,1463]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B910EAF12B76FFB922EEFA67FB4987BE" box="[1160,1220,1438,1463]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Syllis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
